{{Year in Sri Lanka|1992}}

The following lists events that happened during '''[[1992]] in [[Sri Lanka]]'''.

==Incumbents==
*[[President of Sri Lanka|President]]: [[Ranasinghe Premadasa]]

==Events==
* Mylanthanai massacre takes place on 9 August 1992 when 35 minority [[Sri Lankan Tamils]], including 14 children, at [[Mylanthanai]] in [[Batticaloa]] District in [[Sri Lanka]], were killed.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/low/south_asia/2515295.stm|title=Mylanthanai case|accessdate=2006-01-08 |work=BBC | date=November 26, 2002}}</ref>
* A series of attacks take place on civilians in the villages of Alanchipothana, Karapola, Madurangala and Muthugal in eastern [[Polonnaruwa District]], Sri Lanka on 29 April 1992 leaving 157 dead.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sri Lanka: Deliberate killings of Muslim and Tamil villagers in Polonnaruwa|url=http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&id=CBABB2C2398D0E9B802569A6006028CF|publisher=[[Amnesty International]]|access-date=2015-08-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110222090212/http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&id=CBABB2C2398D0E9B802569A6006028CF|archive-date=2011-02-22|dead-url=yes|df=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web| authorlink = | title = SRI LANKA:When will justice be done?| work = | publisher = [[Amnesty International]]| date = 2007| url = http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&id=20111862A3924158802569A6006050A3| format = | doi = | accessdate = 2007-07-19| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20070714022250/http://www.amnestyusa.org/document.php?lang=e&id=20111862A3924158802569A6006050A3| archive-date = 2007-07-14| dead-url = yes| df = }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Chapter 7 - MASSACRES IN THE POLONNARUWA DISTRICT|url=http://www.uthr.org/Reports/Report11/chapter7.htm|work=Report 11|publisher=[[University Teachers for Human Rights]]}}</ref>

